comments.body:
@djukic14 , you are the one that has put in the work to create this tool, which does provide sophisticated coloring capabilities, so I am in favor of any final decisions being made by you. I do believe it would be beneficial to the community to do the following:

- Move the package to the JuliaGraphs organization (with you being the owner of the package of course), so that if the single maintainer of such generically name package disappears there is someone else who can help with maintenance.
- Sometime soon make sure that the package can be easily used as a backend for Graphs.jl coloring (I will post an issue to your package about that shortly) and have the documentation of Graphs.jl refer to GraphColoring.jl as a way to access more coloring algorithms.

Given that this seems to be a package implementing significantly more capabilities on graph coloring than other parts of the ecosystem, I think it is warranted to take a high profile name in the General registry namespace -- I am in favor of accepting the registration.

@djukic14 , this is almost a silly question, but it is helpful to have explicit confirmation when managing the future of the General registry namespace -- could you confirm you will be welcoming to contributions of additional coloring algorithms to your package (so that it can be a home for this type of algorithms in the Graphs.jl ecosystem)?
